2.1 PROJECT

burden analysis extendend gene region (including regulatory) in sporadic breast cancer in diverse ancestries

2.2 OBJECTIVE

plot gene regions

2.3 Genome Build

Plot will be output in hg38 Input are in: - MONSTER.snplist: variants included in gene-specific aggregation test -> hg19 - gene models: retrieved gene tracks from biomart -> hg38 - BCAC GWAS results: -> hg19

2.8 define functions

> # function to read and format MONSTER snplist file data containing all markers
> # and their weights which are included in MONSTER run for specific gene and
> # cohort
> read_format_MONSTER_snplist = function(cohort, gene, gene_id, chainfile = chain_hg19_hg38_path) {
+     # create dir path to cohort mummy logs
+     tardir = paste0(INPUTFOLDER, "/mummy_log/tars/", cohort)
+ 
+     # get name of archive
+     file = list.files(path = tardir, pattern = paste0("^", gene_id, "_"), full.names = T)
+ 
+     # if file for cohort not available return empty data.frame
+     if (length(file) == 0) {
+ 
+         out = data.frame(chr = NA_character_, pos_hg19 = NA_real_, pos_hg38 = NA_real_, 
+             variant_ID = NA_character_, CHROM = NA_real_, A1 = NA_character_, A2 = NA_character_, 
+             SNPweight = NA_real_, cohort = NA_character_, gene = NA_character_)
+ 
+     } else {
+ 
+         # in case of multiple hits take newest file
+         newest_file = file[order(file.mtime(file), decreasing = T)][1]
+ 
+         # MONSTER SNPlist file name
+         snpfile = paste0(basename(newest_file), "/MONSTER.snplist.txt") %>% str_replace(pattern = ".tar.gz", 
+             replacement = "")
+ 
+         # untar single file from archive
+         untar(tarfile = newest_file, files = snpfile, exdir = TMPDIR)
+ 
+         # read MONSTER snplist file in
+         X <- read.delim(paste0(TMPDIR, snpfile), header = F, stringsAsFactors = F)
+         # clean first column values which contain SNPset meta data
+         X[1, 1] <- str_replace(X[1, 1], pattern = "SNPlist01 1   ", replacement = "")
+         X[2, 1] <- str_replace(X[2, 1], pattern = "SNPlist01 1   ", replacement = "")
+ 
+         # format SNPlist data
+         X2 = data.frame(variant_ID = X[1, ] %>% unlist(), SNPweight = X[2, ] %>% 
+             unlist() %>% as.character() %>% as.numeric()) %>% # separate the SNP identifier
+         separate(col = variant_ID, into = c("CHROM", "POS.tmp", "A1", "A2"), sep = "_", 
+             remove = F, convert = TRUE) %>% # give position correct format
+         mutate(pos_hg19 = as.numeric(as.character(POS.tmp))) %>% # add annotation
+         mutate(cohort = cohort, gene = gene) %>% dplyr::select(-POS.tmp)
+ 
+         # make liftOver input format
+         X2.lift = X2 %>% mutate(chr = paste0("chr", CHROM)) %>% dplyr::select(chr, 
+             pos_hg19)
+ 
+         # liftOver from hg19 to hg38
+         out = lift_hg19_hg38(data = X2.lift, chain = chainfile) %>% # combine with hg19 data
+         left_join(X2, by = "pos_hg19")
+     }
+ 
+     # return output
+     return(out)
+ }
> 
> 
> # query biomart to get all coding genes in chromosomal region !!ATTENTION:
> # chromosomal region needs to be given as CHR:START:END and NOT CHR:START-END
> query_genes_in_region_biomart_hg38 = function(gene, region, mart = ensembl) {
+ 
+     # set attributes that should be output
+     attributes.chosen = c("ensembl_gene_id", "chromosome_name", "start_position", 
+         "end_position", "strand", "external_gene_name", "external_gene_source", "gene_biotype")
+ 
+     # preform data query
+     out = getBM(attributes = attributes.chosen, filters = "chromosomal_region", values = region, 
+         mart = ensembl)
+ 
+     out.protein_coding = out %>% filter(gene_biotype == "protein_coding") %>% # make boolean variable whether gene on forward strand, necessary for
+     # geom_gene_arrows
+     mutate(direction = strand == 1) %>% mutate(gene_of_interest = external_gene_name == 
+         gene)
+ 
+     return(out.protein_coding)
+ }
